At least one person was killed when a small Russian  passenger plane crashed at the Berlin-Schoenefeld airport Friday during a  rehearsal flight ahead of the Berlin airshow opening this week, airshow  officials said.
The plane, a JAK 58 which can carry six passengers, crashed on landing,  they added.
It was unclear whether more than one person died. Border police said one  was killed and one injured, but Potsdam police said two had died.
